              cooperatives, so eliminating group certification, will drive =
thousands=20
              of family farmers out of business while giving large-scale co=
mmercial=20
              coffee plantations a competitive advantage. Though the OCA su=
pports=20
              careful monitoring of all organic farms, we are adamantly opp=
osed=20
              to the elimination of group certification for low-income farm=
 cooperatives.=20
              <br>
              <font size=3D"1"><b>Learn more and take action: </b><a href=
=3D"http://alerts.organicconsumers.org/trk/click?ref=3Dzqtbkk3um_1-a4x3134x=
3340774&" target=3D"_blank">http://www.organicconsumers.org/rd=
/usda-coop.c=
fm</a></font></font></td>
            </tr>
            </table>
